The Alex Shutdown Movement held a meeting last night after houses were demolished last week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Alexandra residents aren't backing down. The Alex Shutdown Movement held a meeting on Thursday night after houses were demolished last week. The movement is threatening to shut down Sandton and disrupt businesses. WATCH: EFF testifies at Alexandra inquiry Alexandra resident Thembeni Manana they are planning to reclaim their dignity by occupying land. “We are going to occupy the land, we are going to disturb capital in Sandton City to say you’re making of us, importing labour and there is nothing you are bringing back to us as a community,” Manana said.